<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/24063:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-09T19:00:00-04:00">September
                                    9, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>553. Your 1314, Sept. 7, 7 p.m. Report of your conversation with M. Laval
                            as given to the press here<note n="93" xml:id="d197fn93">For text of
                                press release, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, September 12, 1942, p. 750.</note> was published
                            in Radio Bulletin no. 212 of September 8.</p>
                        <p>You will make occasion to state that the American Government approves
                            your statement as the official reply to M. Laval’s protest.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>